<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="546" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1103,1488]" pageId="3" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1103,1128]" pageId="3" pageNumber="546">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[284,457,1103,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Acanthocaudus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[284,457,1103,1128]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="546">Acanthocaudus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1098,1103,1128]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aphidiinae">Aphidiinae</taxonomicName>
with species in the Nearctic Region using data in the key to New World genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[792,917,1140,1165]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aphidiinae">Aphidiinae</taxonomicName>
in van 
<bibRefCitation author="Achterberg" box="[1011,1225,1140,1165]" pageId="3" pageNumber="546" refString="Van Achterberg, C. (1997) Subfamily Aphidiinae. In: Wharton, R. A., Marsh, P. M. &amp; Sharkey, M. J. (Eds.), Manual of the New World Genera of the Family Braconidae (Hymenoptera). Special Publication No. 1. International Society of Hymenopterists, Washington, D. C., pp. 118 - 131." type="book chapter" year="1997">Achterberg (1997)</bibRefCitation>
: forewing without marginal and submarginal cells, tergum 1 and sternum 1 fused basally at least to level of spiracles, hypopygium of female with prongs, hypopygium of female with accessory prongs at base of hypopygial prongs, and female with at least terga 6–7 with subapical row of pegs or spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
